Interface Traceable

All Known Implementing Classes:
ContextDimension, ContextDimension_IntervalValue, DescriptionSection, DescriptorUnit, DiscussionPosting, DiscussionTopic, DocumentedKnowledge, Effect, Effect_DownstreamEffect, Effect_MolecularInitiatingEvent, EffectopediaObject, IDs, Lab, Link, Link_EffectToEffect, Link_SubstanceToMIE, Pathway, PathwayElement, PathwaySegment, Reference, ReferenceID, ReferenceIDs, Substance, Substance_Chemical, Test
public interface Traceable

Traceable interface provides a mean for tagging IndexedObject descendents which are monitored in EditHistory class. When a field of IndexedObject descendents is modified by its setter user action is recorded containing information about: object that was modified ( objectId ), reference to the archive copy of the previous state ( objectArchiveId ), object class objectClassId, action type objectActionId, date time location stampId, and user userId;

Version:
1.0 @(#)Traceable.java 1.0
Author:
Hristo Aladjov
See Also:
IndexedObject, EditHistory, UserAction
